title: Detailed study of the intermediate structure in the Np-237 fission cross-section. Determination of the fission barrier parameters

x4freetext: Thesis at Univ.Paris-Sud, Orsay.
This work constitutes a follow-up
to the measurement of Np-237 total and fission
cross-section performed at Saclay by D.Paya and
described in his thesis to Univ. Paris-Sud, Orsay.
See last reference below.
In accordance with Paya`s instruction his fission
cross-section is superseded by present work.
Only fission cross-section has been measured by the
author who,however, uses the Paya total cross-sect.
in the analysis of his data and for deducting the
resonance parameters.
In the present work the energy range has also been
broadened to about 35 keV.

Detailed study of the intermediate structure in the
Np-237 fission cross-section. Determination of the
fission barrier parameters
60 MeV Saclay Electron Linear Accel.
2/3 of neutrons from (gamma,n),1/3 from
(gamma,fiss) bombarding natural uranium target
with electrons.
.Six samples grouped two by two on three parallel
planes at 12.5 cm each. Each sample consists of a
semicircular Al foil (16 cm diameter, 10 micron
thick) carrying 2.0 millig/cm**2 of Np-237.
.Total mass of Np-237 was 2.3 gram
.Correction for three flight distances taken into
account.
Time-of-flight, 22.28 m flight-path between
the neutron source and the 2nd Np-237 plate.
.Background was evaluated by black resonance method
using Al (35 keV), Mn (2.38 keV, 337 eV), Co (131 eV)
and boral (0.7-0.65 eV) filters.
Gas scintillator (mixture of He and 2%
nitrogen) operating at liquid nitrogen temperature
to reduce Doppler broadening.
BF3 counter to measure the incident
neutron spectrum.
Fission fragments.
thesis at Univ.
Paris-Sud,Orsay.  The fission cross-section measured
in the present work has been normalized to the Paya
measurement by reproducing the areas of 30.39 and
41.33 eV resonances. The Paya data have been in turn
normalized to U-235 fission cross-section.
After careful chemical analysis of U-Np sample
used by Paya in his measurement,however, it was
realized that the U-235 content was 0.5+-0.05%
instead of the supposed 0.8%.
A further re-normalization has therefore been
performed by multiplying all results by 5/8.
.Statistical error given.

x4freetext: Shape analysis, single level Breit-Wigner.
The good resolution plus small background assured a
detailed analysis around 40 eV where a new resonance
(Er=39.69 eV) could be identified.
Due to the very small value of the fiss. X-sect.
the transmission data measured by Paya had also
to be used in the analysis.
The data are taken from table III in the thesis
Table III gives also total and scattering widths
but they are not compiled here because they have
been taken by the author from the Paya`s  work
(see MONIT-REF)
